cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.COM 

The paper discusses the capacity of cellular networks using Massive MIMO technology, which falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) aspects. The paper specifically focuses on the use of MMSE precoding/combining (cs.MM) and the impact of pilot contamination on capacity. Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the results for communication systems (cs.COM).
